main event: On September 3, 1966, witnesses observed five stationary star-like objects in the sky over Brunswick, Maine for a duration of 13 hours.
interesting points: Witnesses described the objects as having reddish and bluish colors,One witness reported that the objects seemed to change size and appeared and disappeared,The observations were consistent with that of an astronomical phenomenon,The objects did not distort or move throughout the observation period,No photographs were taken during the sightings.
witness description: Witnesses observed the objects using binoculars, which only made the objects appear larger but did not provide further details.
